  "faq": {
    "title": "Frequently Asked Questions",
    "items": [
      {
        "question": "What is Checkin-OK.be?",
        "answer": "Checkin-OK.be is an online platform that helps Belgian companies automatically generate NSSO-compliant attendance declarations for Checkinatwork and CIAO. Upload your CSV or Excel, and we do the rest."
      },
      {
        "question": "What files can I upload?",
        "answer": "You can upload CSV and Excel files (.xlsx) containing your employee attendance data. The system automatically recognizes the column layout and validates the data."
      },
      {
        "question": "How does the AI correction work?",
        "answer": "Our AI module (Azure GPT-4o) automatically detects and corrects typos in NISS/BIS numbers, extracts timestamps from natural language, and separates concatenated fields. You always maintain control via the resolution matrix."
      },
      {
        "question": "Is my data safe?",
        "answer": "Absolutely. All personal data is processed exclusively in volatile memory. There is no database storage of names, NISS, BIS, or Limosa numbers. We are fully GDPR and GBA compliant."
      },
      {
        "question": "Do I need to create an account?",
        "answer": "No, you can start immediately without an account. For advanced features like conversion history and priority support, a Business subscription is available."
      },
      {
        "question": "How do I export to NSSO XML?",
        "answer": "After uploading and validating your data, click 'Generate NSSO XML'. The system generates XSD v1.13-compliant payloads for both Checkinatwork and CIAO, ready for submission to the NSSO."
      }
    ]
  },
